Databricks Notebook: Read CSV from Azure Blob (No Mount)
🔹 Step 1: Set Storage Configuration
# Azure Storage details
container = "srccontainer"
storageAccount = "src2603"
accessKey = "YOUR_ACCESS_KEY"   # 🔴 replace with your real key

# Spark config key
accountKey = f"fs.azure.account.key.{storageAccount}.blob.core.windows.net"

# Set configuration
spark.conf.set(accountKey, accessKey)

print("✅ Storage configured successfully")
🔹 Step 2: Verify Connection (List Files)
# List files in container
path = f"wasbs://{container}@{storageAccount}.blob.core.windows.net/"

files = dbutils.fs.ls(path)
display(files)

👉 This step helps confirm:

Container exists ✅
File name is correct ✅
🔹 Step 3: Read CSV File
# Correct file path (NO duplicate container, NO double .csv)
file_path = f"wasbs://{container}@{storageAccount}.blob.core.windows.net/usd_to_eur.csv"

# Read CSV
df = spark.read.csv(file_path, header=True, inferSchema=True)

display(df)
🔹 Step 4: Basic Data Checks
# Show schema
df.printSchema()

# Show top 5 rows
df.show(5)

# Count rows
print("Row count:", df.count())
🔹 Step 5: Example Transformations
# Example: Select specific columns
df.select("*").show(5)

# Example: Filter data (modify column name as per your file)
# df.filter(df["rate"] > 1.0).show()
🔹 Step 6: Save as Table (Optional)
# Save as managed table
df.write.mode("overwrite").saveAsTable("usd_to_eur_table")

# Query table
display(spark.sql("SELECT * FROM usd_to_eur_table"))
🔹 Step 7: Save as Parquet (Optional)
output_path = f"wasbs://{container}@{storageAccount}.blob.core.windows.net/output/usd_to_eur_parquet"

df.write.mode("overwrite").parquet(output_path)

print("✅ Data saved as Parquet")
